  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 32 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 680 mg
course: main course
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/pan-seared-duck-breast-5cf032079d4b2a000d4f80cb
time required: 35 minutes
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
---

Wash and dry all produce. Halve @fingerling potatoes{12%oz} lengthwise. Place in a
#medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and
cook until easily pierced with a fork, ~{12-15%minutes}. Drain well, then return
potatoes to pot. Meanwhile, trim and discard woody ends from
@asparagus{6%oz}. Mince @chives{1/4%oz}.

Pat @duck breasts{12%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Place skin sides down in a #large pan{}. Cook over medium heat until
skin is crisp and most of the fat has rendered, ~{15-20%minutes}, pouring off and
reserving fat as it renders. Flip duck and cook to desired doneness, about
~{5%minutes} more. Transfer to a #cutting board{} and let rest.

> TIP: Lower heat if skin begins to brown too quickly.

Add just enough reserved duck fat to pot with potatoes to cover bottom surface.
Heat pot over medium-high heat and cook, stirring, until potatoes are browned
and crisp, ~{3-5%minutes}. Remove from pot and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, add asparagus and @water{2%tsp} to pan used for duck over medium heat.
Cover and steam until bright green, ~{2-4%minutes}. Uncover, then increase heat to
medium-high and add a drizzle of duck fat and @grape tomatoes{4%oz}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until asparagus is tender and tomatoes burst, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Transfer to a #plate{} and set aside.

Stir @chicken demi-glace{1} and @water{1/4%cup} and @butter{2%tbsp} into same pan.
Bring to a boil, then remove from heat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Slice duck crosswise. Divide between #plates{} along with potatoes and veggies. Spoon
sauce over everything. Sprinkle with chives.